Prerequisites:
- install OpenFOAM-12; manual install uses branch `version-12` from repository https://github.com/OpenFOAM/OpenFOAM-dev.git
- install Paraview-5.9.0;
-- use https://www.paraview.org/paraview-downloads/download.php?submit=Download&version=v5.9&type=binary&os=Linux&downloadFile=ParaView-5.9.0-osmesa-MPI-Linux-Python3.8-64bit.tar.gz for cluster runs

See file script/config.sh and change directories to location of your installed packages
See also templates/run.sh before running `prepare_*.sh` if you want to change cluster run parameters

Use scripts from scripts/ folder -- run them from base directory!
- run `scripts/prepare_*.sh`to setup each of experiment series
- run `scripts/launch_*.sh` to submit a batch job (sbatch)
- run `scripts/anim*.sh` to draw the results as images (then use tools such as `ffmpeg` to create videos from images)
